[size=4][b]What[/b][/size]

[size=3]Lifts the vanilla "one sermon per week" rule and gives you fine-grained control over how much the church costs to run.[/size]

[size=3][b]Frequency[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][size=3][b]Multiple sermons per day[/b] — remove the once-per-day cap and run sermons as often as you like.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Every day[/b] — remove the once-per-week cap on running sermons for faith.[/size]
[/list]

[size=3][b]Cost modes[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][size=3][b]Standard mode[/b] — every repeat sermon consumes the prayer you used, except for the most basic tier (which stays free-to-reuse, matching vanilla's default behaviour).[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Alternate mode[/b] — instead of losing the prayer outright, there's a 20% / 40% / 60% chance (tier-based) that the prayer downgrades one tier. Easier mid-term sustainability if you don't want to re-craft higher-tier prayers every session.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Cheat mode[/b] — pray freely with no loss and no downgrade. Overrides the two modes above. "Speed up time" still applies if you want cutscenes to fly by.[/size]
[/list]

[size=3][b]Pacing[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][size=3][b]Speed up time during sermons[/b] — shrinks the in-game time the sermon cutscene takes. Useful when running many per day.[/size]
[/list]

[size=3]No unlock required — the mod activates as soon as you have church access in vanilla (after the starter quest and tech unlocks that give you a pulpit).[/size]

[size=4][b]Other mods of mine you might like[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/87]Keepers Candles[/url] — candles never burn out, stay lit. Ideal for a busy sermon routine.[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/57]Queue Everything[/url] — includes an opt-in per-workbench auto-craft for Sermons, so the pulpit can run on its own.[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/55]Misc. Bits and Bobs[/url] — includes the "Evict Church Visitors" button if the congregation gets stuck.[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/42]Exhaust-less[/url] — half-cost sanity and energy options, helpful if praying often.[/size]
[/list]

[size=4][b]Configuration[/b][/size]

[size=3]If you installed the required [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/79]Graveyard Keeper BepInEx 5 Pack[/url] and this mod is configurable, press F1 in-game to open the config interface.[/size]

[size=4][b]Requirements[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/79][size=3]Graveyard Keeper BepInEx 5 Pack at Graveyard Keeper Nexus - Mods and community (nexusmods.com)[/size][/url]
[/list]
[size=4][b]Installation[/b][/size]

[size=3]Installation using Vortex is the recommended installation method. If you wish to install manually, extract the contents of the mod archive into:

[code]...&#92;steamapps&#92;common&#92;Graveyard Keeper&#92;BepInEx[/code][/size]

